LAGO primarily provides venture debt financing customized to meet your particular needs as you scale your business, be it working capital, asset purchases, operating expenses, acquisitions, or other strategic growth initiatives. Our debt products are designed to work in concert with sponsors’ existing equity investment, at a lower cost and dilution, to prolong the period to future equity raises and debt refinancings. Here's a bit more below about what we do.

After 11 years building a $60MM metabolic optimization company self-funded (50% YoY rev growth, 64% recurring revenue, a 200+ team), we’re now exploring doing a large (for us) fundraise, and looking to align ourselves with good people we can trust who know our space, can grok our vision, advise on capital structure/strategy, run the fundraising process and become a great long-term strategic growth partner.

We recently purchased the Metabolic.com domain so we can officially own our positioning. We will rebrand to simply “Metabolic” in 2 months, launch our new website and app shortly thereafter, integrating into a unified UX all those solutions we’ve developed separately to date. We laser focus on metabolism simply because we’ve found that when you get that dialed in, your cells get the energy they need to do their jobs right, allowing your entire body to thrive.

We’ve substantially de-risked the business, having done $212MM in rev to date, spent $70MM in paid online acquisition, acquired 40MM leads, 1.5MM buyers and have a multi-channel (DTC, retail, practitioner, corporate, etc.) growth plan to become a multi-billion $ business by 2025.

Our team, alongside external accountants, has done a solid job maintaining our books on a modified cash basis through a series of fundraises over the past couple of years. As we enter our next phase of growth, we're looking to engage an accounting firm to work with us on three initiatives:

- Perform a diagnostic of our historical books / systems, providing a report on findings (issues, improvements, recommendations, etc.) and providing advice on several more specific items (phantom stock, founder stock, options, convertible notes, equity investments, etc.)
- Shift our system from a modified cash basis to an accrual basis
- Provide an overview of bookkeeping services offered that would maintain our books on an monthly basis as well as additional consulting services on accounting related activities (R&D credits, EOY taxes, etc)

We received a proposal to assist in a vendor tax due diligence of a Belgian target company: Mediagenix Next Generation NV.

Because this entity has a 100% US subsidiary, Mediagenix Corporation, we kindly ask you wether you are interested to assist us with the tax due diligence, as far as this US entity is concerned?

The scope would in principle entail the following:

- Scan of trial balances and tax declarations, for the accounting years where the relevant statute of limitations has not yet expired and a scan of the relevant VAT returns.
- A high level review of the transfer pricing policy and past legal restructurings/acquisition structures (if any).
- past tax audits (if any) and identify potential material (>€50k) issues in CTX, VAT and payroll taxes per issue per year.
- Based thereon, report on key issues and potential tax cash optimization opportunities to be covered in the vendor assistance report.
- Review of tax compliance environment of the US subsidiary (historic filing position, relationship with tax authority, any past tax audits etc.);
Based on the information we currently have, the US entity is a mere sales / rep. Office from the Belgian parent company. Given the materiality limit of 50k EUR, the scope/work for each subsidiary should be rather limited in our opinion.

We have to communicate a fee proposal today (Central Europe Time). We are aware this is at short notice. Therefore, could you please respond you fee quote upon your earliest convenience?

p.s; We listed below in bullet point the information we currently have in this respect.

I propose to have a call to discuss further in detail (if required).

Client Description: ACCOUNTING: > Get the current Series LLC for your first property set up with diligence-ready books > Have that team setup templates and processes to replicate the same structures for future Series LLCs to come > If helpful, that same team can plug into the parent C-Corp's books and processes as well, making sure that those books stay diligence/audit-ready and provide you with overall health reporting of the C-Corp > This team will be comprised of a Controller, Senior Accountant, and Staff Accountant - the workload being a little top-heavy in months 1 & 2, but progressing to a cost-effective bottom-heavy workload by month 3 for ongoing accounting and operational support  FINANCE: > Build a strong bottom-up financial model. This model would become the central "tent-pole" living document for planning/measuring for you and your management team, and act as a communication tool with future investors and board members > Create a dashboard (web-based) that would measure and display key/actionable KPIs for your team to monitor, discuss, and use for prioritizing needed actions to meet targets. This dashboard would pull live data from existing and future data sources (think: Quickbooks, your production system, Google Analytics, CRMs, etc.). > This team is probably a strong Senior Financial Analyst to handle most of the modeling and monthly maintenance work, paired with a seasoned CFO from our team to add value as needed and become your financial sparring partner and sounding board on-demand
Deal Description:
ACCOUNTING:
 > Get the current Series LLC for your first property set up with diligence-ready books
 > Have that team setup templates and processes to replicate the same structures for future Series LLCs to come

 > This team will be comprised of a Controller, Senior Accountant, and Staff Accountant - the workload being a little top-heavy in months 1 & 2, but progressing to a cost-effective bottom-heavy workload by month 3 for ongoing accounting and operational support
 
 FINANCE:

 > This team is probably a strong Senior Financial Analyst to handle most of the modeling and monthly maintenance work, paired with a seasoned CFO from our team to add value as needed and become your financial sparring partner and sounding board on-demand

Client Description: Standalone books - team approach would be very beneficial in creating standalone books for Korea and Singapore; can utilize controller, Sr. account and staff accountant to reduce avg bill rate - Korea - about 150 to 200 hours for 2018 and 2019 combined - variable for estimated time is based on level of completeness for supporting documentation - how much back-up and detail is available - Singapore - about 40 to 60 hours for 2018 and 2019 combined  Global Consolidation Preparation - Step 1: US standalone book inter-company transactions - estimated at 30 to 40 hours. The variable on time would be the existing status of the US book management. Understanding that you have audit and year-end prep level of detail requirements, it may require the practice of 'reverse' consolidation + inter-company account reconciliation with subsidiaries - Step 2: Generate manual global consolidation report - 15 to 20 hours. the practice includes foreign currency translation on standalone book, inter-company elimination entry preparation, etc.   NetSuite data entry and migration - dual system - enter completed 2018 and 2019 subsidiary data as standalone financial results (from QBO) to NetSuite. Estimation is 30 to 60 hours; range depends on different approaches - Note that hour estimation does not include the support during NetSuite system implementation - as in running accounting in QB in parallel to in-house team learning NetSuite. This would require further details on current Moloco full cycle accounting (operation, closing, etc) workflow.   Total estimated hours as understood/scoped above - 300 to 400 hours.   This project is expected to take 8-10 weeks. This estimated time frame is dependent to some degree on having access to Company’s information as requested and team members as needed as well as Consultant’s understanding of the scope of services necessary at the time of entering into this Agreement.    Standalone books for foreign subsidiaries. 4-6 weeks Global consolidation preparation: 2-3 weeks Dual system data entry - 1-2 weeks

Client Description: (1) re-structuring the company as a VC/PE firm into 3 LLC's We would help manage this process by first meeting with one of the corporate tax advisors and/or corporate attorneys that we work closely with. After we get the proper guidance, we would then implement with help from legal as needed.  (2) setting up accounting software for the new LLC structure,  We would assign an accounting team to set up the proper accounting infrastructure and procedures, as well as manage the day to day and perform the monthly accounting close going forward   (3) publish Cap Table,  We would own and maintain this for you as well. As with our approach to accounting - we like to utilize the best in class technology solutions that are available. Currently, we use a platform called Carta to maintain and track cap tables. The cash distribution and remaining amounts from investor commitments we track and update in real time using google sheets or excel.   (4) publishing quarterly statements,  Yes, we will create quarterly reports and statements. This would be a function of the CFO and analyst with help from the accounting team we mentioned in #2 above  (5) annual tax preparation.  ... and/or annual audit.  This is a great example of one of the processes that we manage. We would begin by getting quotes for the tax return work and the audit if needed. Some of the audit/tax firms that we work with provide special pricing for our clients and even have dedicated teams to work on our returns. Once we make a decision on who to work with, we manage and help the team on their side by providing the necessary reports, fielding their questions, preparing the PBC items for their review, etc.   As for next steps, I like the idea of setting up a budget and starting in on the list above - specifically #1, 2 and 3. This will give us a good idea of what the effort is going to look like going forward and what technology, process, and procedures we need to establish up front.
